r experiments in skin-grafted lymphopenic animals revealed a direct regulatory role for the \u03b17nAChR on T cells. Taken together, our data demonstrate that the cholinergic pathway regulates alloreactivity and transplantation tolerance at multiple levels. One implication suggested by our work is that, in an organ transplant setting, deliberate \u03b17nAChR stimulation of brain dead donors might be a valuable approach for preventing donor tissue inflammation prior to transplant.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Sadis, Claude", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Detienne, Sophie", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Vokaer, Beno??t", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Charbonnier, Louis Marie", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lema??tre, Philippe", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Spilleboudt, Chlo??", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Delbauve, Sandrine", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kubjak, Carole", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Flamand, V??ronique", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Field, Kenneth A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Goldman, Michel", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Benghiat, Fleur S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Le Moine, Alain", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Transcriptome", "Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/829f14c452120dcb8abae4426d594111", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/210637ab0de233ebf78c3c1906ac7f4062d7ee5fd69fd2374810da861475feca", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/UW3FFAT7", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/UW3FFAT7", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/c486b44c477a50773fd3d611dee183d4!/b42947-45557", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa